##When the outbreak came, I took my wife and daughter to live in the mountains

Micro Signal Zhenshigushi1

Feature description, a true story every day that touches the heart of the original.

Returning from the city to the countryside for the Lunar New Year, Allín's wife and daughter came down with cold symptoms. In Stuck in the Middle, Allín took his wife and daughter into the mountains and spent 14 days in isolation, setting up temporary shelters in the wilderness far from the city.

Year: 2020

Venue: Yung on town, Liuzhou

At eight in the morning on the fourth day of the first lunar month, Allín got up from the cold wet ground, picked up a handful of firewood and threw it into the brick oven. As the water in the pot bubbled and he warmed himself a little, he went into the hut and warmed his hands, putting the backs of his hands on the foreheads of his wife and daughter. Yeah, no fever.

He heaved a sigh of relief. Seeing the two men still asleep, he went back to the stove, filled a bottle of boiling water to wash his face, grabbed a handful of noodles and put them in the pot. He habitually clicked on his cell phone to see how many more confirmed cases there were today.

It was his first morning in the mountains with his wife and daughter.

Allín wasn't supposed to be with them on New Year's. The original plan, the wife and daughter will stay in Liuzhou, a few days before the New Year shopping, to see the city's Spring Festival activities, the third day to attend cousin's wedding in Jiangxi home. On December twenty-eight, Allín and his youngest son, Dong Zai, returned to their hometown in Rong'an County.

The day after he returned home, the city of Wuhan was closed. News of the pneumonia spread, he quickly called his wife to return the ticket back to Jiangxi, but heard a cough from the other end of the phone. The quiet life of a family is suddenly shattered.

His wife, a Yan, and their daughter, Xin Xin, had a cold years ago. They thought it was just a cold, so they took some medicine. But when they thought of the new type of pneumonia, a cough and a fever, Allín suddenly felt nervous.

I don't know if it's the common cold or the new pneumonia. The city has a confirmed case, home without masks, alcohol and other items, they left alone in the city no one to take care of, but also out to buy vegetables, the risk of infection is very high. Take back home is not good, there are more than 60-year-old parents and 3-year-old son, in case it is pneumonia, the family can be infected.

The first day of the New Year, village cadres go door to door notice not to go out, not to party, the village has no trace of the new year atmosphere. After a long day of tossing and turning, Allín decided to take his wife and daughter up the mountain to live in the orchard for a while, so he could take care of them and not worry about infecting his family.

The next night, ah Yan ran away and packed up her daily necessities. Allín didn't sleep well, either. He rushed to the city early in the morning, loaded everything he could find in the rental house into his car, stopped at the supermarket to buy some vegetables, noodles, and preserved chicken. He didn't dare go home to say goodbye, either. He took his wife and daughter and headed for the mountains.

Drive down the country road, cross a river, and up the hill is Allín's orchard. Allín and his wife had to get out of their car, which was stuck uphill in the mud of a rainy mountain road. After a few hundred meters, they had to carry their things a dozen times, and they were panting with fatigue.

And this is just the beginning of life in the mountains.

Map | mountain road

The cabin in the orchard served as a temporary hideout for Allín, his wife, and their daughter. There was nothing in the triangular area between the CRISTAE and the walls, and Allín looked at the empty wooden house with the melancholy of something to be done.

After taking his things into the house, he took a little rest, and then quickly set up, trying to get a place to eat and sleep before it got dark.

He spread several thick quilts on the floor for the mother and daughter to sleep in, and dragged a few thick tree trunks on both sides of the wall outside the House, covered with red and blue old plastic cloth, while doing their own "bedroom" , while doing the kitchen. Then he dug a hole in the ground, laid two or three bricks to keep off the wind, and set up a simple stove.

Allín's kitchen

"Why did we come to live here, Dad? " Asked her 7-year-old daughter, Yan Xin, as she pulled Allín's sleeve up from her warm home

"There's a virus out there, you get sick when you catch it, and we live in the mountains, and you can't get sick if you don't touch people outside, " Allín said as he comforted her, dragging the battery from the battery car into the House and using an inverter to connect the battery to the incandescent lamp, then use the thin trunk to lift the lamp to a high place. Five batteries and a lithium-ion battery, it'll probably survive the quarantine.

"Why don't GRANDPA, grandma and little brother come with us? " Xinxin asked. The sudden change made her a little uneasy.

Allín wiped her hands, pinched her daughter's palm and pressed it against her forehead to test the temperature. "they're safe at home. We'll go down in a few days. " She nodded obediently.

It was getting dark, the temperature in the mountains was dropping, the wind was blowing, and Allín began to heat the water. The water was drawn directly from the Stream, the stove was not strict, the fire was not concentrated, and it took half an hour to boil. He counted the portions and laid a handful of noodles, which he cooked until they were soft. Then he put in a handful of vegetables and two eggs.

Allín tossed and turned for more than an hour over the usual minutes of cooking. The three of them each filled a bowl of noodles and sat around eating in the hut, talking occasionally. The fire on the stove outside the hut was still burning, making the forest even darker.

To avoid contact as much as possible, Allín had his wife and daughter sleep in the house, and he slept outside. The mountain temperature is low, only three or four degrees at night, the ground is wet and cool, the wind is gusty, although covered with two quilts, he still felt cold, heart occasionally flash mountain beast and ghost legend.

By graphic | ARLIN's bed

Half Asleep by morning, Allín got up and sat by the stove to keep warm. There were misty mountains all around, and it had been raining all the time, and there was always the possibility of flash floods and mudslides. After spending so much time in the city and being suddenly exposed to nature, he began to feel far removed from the inconveniences of modern life.

The rental house in the city is only 16 square meters, old and old, the family of four live crowded, windows and doors pipes are also some problems, but then the Cold Day into the house is also warm, turn on the tap there is hot water, want to eat what the supermarket can buy.

When I lived there, I felt that everything in my life was taken for granted and nothing was hard to find. I was forced into the mountains and found that I could cook and buy food at any time. Now want to cook to go to the mountains to chop wood, want to heat must sit by the fire, even the bath has become a problem...

No matter how much emotion there is, isolation begins inevitably. "I hope ah-yan and hin-yan get well soon, as long as they are healthy, everything else is a little thing, " Allín said to himself as he warmed the fire.

New Crown Pneumonia is like a sword hanging over the head, a cold bad day, the sword may be down at any time. His wife did not pay much attention to the epidemic, his cold is also light, the daughter is naive, told mother and daughter temperature, drink more water, more clothing, became Allín the most important thing every day.

Under Allín's care, the mother and daughter's cold was almost gone in two or three days, but after a while there was a cough, which added to his stress.

To make the mother and daughter sleep more comfortable, he fumbled with bamboo to make a makeshift bed. Four lengths of rope were tied to the slanted trunk, two logs were hung, and the bamboo was cut in half with an axe. The strips were tied to the logs in rows. With bamboo beds, mother and daughter would no longer have to sleep on the ground.

Xin Xin is very naughty, often playing with Allín behind, and sometimes a person to run up the mountain, wearing rain shoes to tread water in the river, covered with mud, feet cold, shouted words are in the left ear and out the right ear, a few days down, and turn into a clay figurine.

Life on the mountain was no easier than in the city, and in order to give hin a hot bath, Allín took the moisture proof cylindrical film of the Husk Valley, cut off a section three meters long, tied the end of the film tightly, stuffed it into a loop of water pipes, and hung it on a branch of a tree, made a simple "bathroom" .

Field baths

Afraid of his daughter's cold, he also turned out the cardboard apple boxes and pressure-resistant Pearl Cotton, made two pairs of Cushions, pad in her rain shoes. Afraid that she had fun in the mountains, but also to supervise her writing winter vacation homework, father and daughter spent more time together than usual a week.

The father is accompanying his daughter and is thinking of his youngest son, Dong Zai. Dong is very dependent on Allín and sleeps with him all the time. On the third day of the eighth lunar month, Allín got up early to go before Dong Zai woke up. If his son had seen him drive away, he would have been crying and would have followed him.

When he contacted his family, Allín never opened the video, afraid to let Dong see them, in case he recognized the cabin and might come running. But even if you can't see dad on the screen, every time you talk to Dong Zai, he listens stubbornly to you and asks him again and again when he will be back.

Allín's father was the only one to deliver supplies while he lived in the mountains. The old man nearly 70 years old, each time carrying dozens of kilograms of fruit, vegetables on foot up the mountain, walk a break, over the river, uphill, to the entrance of the orchard no longer go.

That time he put the bag on the ground, toward the cabin shouted a few times, Xin Xin Xin heard GRANDPA's voice, hurriedly ran out, even called "GRANDPA" , fell also regardless. The grandfather, however, did not come up to hug her as usual, but stood there waving his hand to her and beckoning her to return.

Xin Xin returned to Allín and asked him, "Why is GRANDPA avoiding me? " Allín said, "didn't we come back from the city? We might have the virus, so we don't want to see GRANDPA. "

He pointed to the bag to distract his daughter. "Let's see what's good here. ". Xin Xin grilled the bag, "there are Kumquat, cabbage, Taro, have noodles, " and wheezed.

ALLÍN's father had been here three times, and the food was the happiest of all. Mountain food is too bad, eat tofu skin, kelp and other dried vegetables, meals are vegetables egg noodles, do not know how long to stay in the mountains, bought Bacon is not willing to eat.

Couples delivering food

Allín tried to avoid contact with others and made plans to stay on the mountain for half a month, but went down the mountain on the Sixth Day of the sixth lunar month.

My mother called to say that everyone in the village was picking Fortunella, and that the dealer would take as many as he could, but he had to deliver them as soon as possible, so Allín had to hurry home and pick them together, in case he couldn't sell them later.

Allín went home and picked all day. At 10 p.m. , he got a call from his dealer telling them not to pick the fruit tomorrow.

After answering the phone, Allín, his parents, brother and sister in law quickly dressed and went to the orchard, the night picked Kumquat are finished. Loaded into his car at five in the morning, he drove to town alone, without his family following him as usual.

Wearing a mask, goggles, and raincoat and slacks, Allín armed himself to the teeth as he entered the town. There were not many people in the streets. Young people wore masks. The KUMQUAT collector, chatting without a mask at the warehouse door, saw Allín all dressed up and asked, with half a doubt and half a sneer, "is it so scary? "

Allín smiled innocently, without getting angry, and patiently explained, "it's really scary, it has an incubation period, and no one can be sure it's safe. " It's always good to be more careful, and Allín believed it.

More than 2000 Jin Jin Kumquat boss all received, each jin average price 4 yuan, only the past year price half. Allín thanked his boss and left. He wasn't surprised, but he was sad.

Rongan slippery skin Kumquat is a local specialty, is the main economic source of the town, the village people a year of hard work, all hope to make some money in the new year, who did not expect unexpected changes. Fortunately, the village still has half a dozen families who haven't had time to pick fruit, and Fortunella will rot in the fields before the epidemic is over.

Fortunella in front of the House

Life had once again torn the cruel side of Allín. Like many young people in small towns, after graduating from junior high school, Allín's mother fell ill and the family's finances were strained, so he stopped studying and went out to work.

Over the years, he tried many ways to make a living: working in a factory, opening a breakfast shop with his wife, selling small toys from street to street... but he could barely make ends meet.

As urban management becomes tighter, it is getting harder and harder to run a stall. With a son born, a daughter in school, and elderly parents, Allín, 32, has a growing burden on his shoulders. In order to take care of the children, he and his wife sold the business stall at a low price and found a domestic service job in the city.

Domestic work is not fixed, sometimes a day or two can not receive the order, sometimes a day to work eight or nine hours. Usually monthly income is only about 3,000, deduct rent, children school fees, plus the cost of living, human relations, two people a year also saved what money.

Halving the Kumquat income will make the family more difficult, but Allín did not want to say too much, quietly swallowed all the difficulties, only to say "no money can also earn, the family safe on the line. ".

Family was Allín's greatest ambition, and after more than a decade on the road, he had grown weary of the vagaries of life. Home Beautiful, fresh air, open the door is a large orchard and castle peak. He wants to return to his hometown, but it is difficult to make a living by farming. The medical and educational expenses of the old people and their children will be more and more. If he goes back, he will worry about his family's financial problems and will not be reconciled to his lack of progress.

Allín has been trying to find a way to see the video site on the rural blogger auction rural life, selling local products can make money, he would like to try.

Last June, he set up an account called "Allín's diary, " shooting daily videos like a diary, fixing cars, making wine, taking dogs to explore mountains, cooking home-cooked meals, making homemade fishing gear, and recording all the fun things he had at home, he taught himself to cut and edit music and characters and tried to make a living on the Internet.

During the isolation period on the mountain, with his daughter to build a bamboo bed, home-made "bathroom" , he took a cell phone shot, can not spare hands with sticks and bricks on the phone on the ground. The video was rough, not many people saw it, and he wasn't discouraged, thinking he'd learned a craft somehow.

Half way through the quarantine period, the mother and daughter's cold was almost gone, the manual work was almost done, he began holding a mobile phone slowly cut video. There is no entertainment on the mountain, the couple can only sit playing with their mobile phones, a three-or five-minute short video clip on a few hours, is to kill time.

Xin Xin occasionally kept asking him: "Dad, are we all right? "? Mom and I don't have a cold anymore. Can we go back down? I miss my grandparents,"Allín said, stroking her head."How about a few more days? After two weeks, we'll go down."

He wanted to go down too. He hadn't seen his little boy in a long time. Listen to the mother said the first two days Dongzai often before going to bed, ask dad where to go, say will cry. Allín coaxed him on the phone that he was going to work and would be back in a few days, and he pestered his grandmother to ask how many more days, every day.

When I went home to pick up Fortunella, Allín didn't dare come in. When eating mother put the bowl on the dam, she went to Allín to get it, afraid of infection, also afraid of the son saw to follow him.

On the day of the Lantern Festival, the three of them finally had a big meal. Allín took the reluctant piece of Bacon and cooked it with the beans. He took his hoe and went up the hill to dig up the five fingered peaches and pick the fragrant leaves and put them in the pot.

The stew was supposed to be dinner, but the three of them were so greedy that they ate most of it by noon. He put the bowl of lean meat clip to his daughter, the daughter again clip back, push three or four times, until he said he had eaten, the daughter just eat.

Three days later, the isolation period finally ended, his wife and daughter have no symptoms, no longer worry about infectious family, three people quickly pack things to the car to move, eager to leave the mountains.

The log cabin in the orchard

When they got home, Allín's mother killed a chicken, used all the ingredients in the house, cooked a full table, and the family had a real reunion dinner on the 18th day of the first lunar month.

In the evening, Xin Xin ran to sleep with the grandmother she had not seen for a long time, while Allín stayed with his youngest son. For more than 20 days, he was very nervous. He slept on a wooden bed at home, holding his son, and finally he got a good night's sleep.

- END -

By Wenjing Li
